CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 16, 1957, pg. A2 reads: "Long Service Recognized - On Feb. 8, a group of Fifth Ward Republicans paid honor to Mamie Herbert and Estelle Baber, two of the oldest Republican workers in ward. The home of Mrs. Herbert, 834 Anaheim St., was the meeting place and a sumptuous dinner made everybody happy.  Shown in the above picture are, seated: Ralph V. Miller, Pearl Miller, Mamie Herbert, Estelle Baber, William Wilson.  Standing: David Thompkins, Gloria Miller, John H. Adams, May Toy, Lu Davenport and Lillie Wright.  Martha Moore, prodigy of Mrs. Herbert, could not attend the affair. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, seated: Ralph V. Miller, Pearl Miller, Mamie Herbert, Estelle Baber, and William Wilson; standing: David Thompkins, Gloria Miller, John H. Adams, May Toy, Lu Davenport, and Lillie Wright, gathered around sofa in home of Mamie Herbert, 834 Anaheim Street
